        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n\n- Keep OpenAI outbound queued initial greetings on the active explicit ready-trigger path so the provider sends `conversation.item.create` followed by `response.create` after `session.updated`.\n- Fire the OpenAI `onReady()` callback before draining audio that arrived before `session.updated`, so queued initial greeting suppression reaches the Realtime session before pending caller audio can trigger server VAD.\n- Suppress OpenAI Realtime server-VAD auto responses while a manual response is active, keep suppression in place while a pending retry is queued, then restore the configured auto-response behavior only after the manual turn finishes.\n- Preserve base realtime session instructions instead of moving the queued greeting into `session.update` instructions.\n- Keep non-OpenAI realtime providers on the existing explicit on-ready initial greeting path.\n- No config surface or plugin API surface changed.\n\n## Behavior proof\n\nThe focused regressions cover Omar's active-response requirement and ClawSweeper's pre-ready caller-audio blocker:\n\n- `createBridge(...).instructions` remains the base session instructions (`\"Be helpful.\"`), so the initial greeting is not passively parked in `session.update`.\n- `onReady()` calls `triggerGreeting()` exactly once with the full queued first-turn instruction.\n- The OpenAI provider regression proves `triggerGreeting()` sends one `conversation.item.create`, temporarily updates turn detection to `create_response:false`, sends one `response.create`, and only then drains pre-ready caller audio.\n- A response-error regression proves active-response errors keep suppression active while a pending manual response retry is queued, and restore `create_response:true` after the retried response finishes.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 shards, 72 tests passed\n- `node_modules/oxfmt/bin/oxfmt --check extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts` -> passed\n- `node_modules/oxlint/bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` -> passed\n\nSigned head: `e641b2503794570c6229639ca55a108804493bdb`.\n\nKnown proof gap: no live Twilio/OpenAI outbound call was run in this environment.",
